result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] and Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] was dismissed by the court.

  • Robert M Cimbalnik was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Cases 15CF233, 15CT293, 15TR4434, 15TR4435 and 15TR4436 called together at 10:46am [mo]
Defendant Robert M Cimbalnik in court, in custody with Attorney David Zarwell.   ADA Jeffrey Shock appears for the State of Wisconsin and Jefferson County.
ADA Shock verifies victim rights compliance. 

As to Case 15CF233:
Mr. Cimbalnik waives his right to Preliminary Hearing; the Court accepts this waiver and binds him over for Trial.

Arraignment:
--service of Information admitted, reading waived
--the charges and maximum penalties are recited

Constitutional rights reviewed; maximum penalties recited; plea of "Guilty" entered on Count #1 of Case 15CF233; factual basis stipulated;the Court accepts the plea, finds Mr. Cimbalnik guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Joint Motion of Counsel, the Court reads in and dismisses: Count #2 of Case 15CF233 and Case 15CT293. The Court also orders that cases 15TR4434, 15TR4435 and 15TR4436 be reopened the Judgement vacated. Cases 15TR4434, 15TR4435 and 15TR4436 are read- in and dismissed, as well. 

Sentencing arguments given by Counsel
Statement made by Mr. Cimbalnik
recess: 11:25--reconvene: 11:28 (to allow Court to review documents)

On Count #1 of Case 15CF233:
The Court sentences Mr. Cimbalnik  to  5  years, with an Initial Term of Confinement in Prison of  2  years &  0  months, and the maximum time to serve on Extended Supervision of  3 years &  0  months.  This sentence is to be served CONSECUTIVE to current sentence in being.

The Court finds that the Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program "Boot Camp".
The Court finds that the Defendant is NOT eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.
 

The Court gives   0  days credit for time already served.

The Court orders as conditions of Extended Supervision:
--To pay fine of $1800+ costs= $3,289

The Court orders Mr. Cimbalnik:

--Revocation of drivers license for 36 months
--County alcohol and drug assessment ordered
--Ignition Interlock Device required on any vehicle driven by the Defendant for a 36 month period  


--6 demerit points assessed

The Court determines that Mr. Cimbalnik has already provided a DNA sample and does NOT order Mr. Cimbalnik to provide another sample. 
Felony Firearm and Voting-rights prohibitions/warnings given
Explanation of Determinate Sentence form given to the Defendant
recess: 11:53am
Defendant's Demand and Motion for Discovery and Inspection

[MK] case called at 3:02pm. 
Defendant Robert M Cimbalnik appears via videoconferencing from the Jefferson County Jail, in custody, with Attorney David Zarwell.  ADA Monica Hall appears for the State of Wisconsin.  
On agreement of counsel, the Court finds that the videoconferencing system is sight and sound sufficient. 

Service of Complaint admitted, reading waived, the charges and maximum penalties are recited. 
Preliminary Hearing time limits are waived by both parties.

The Court requires a $2,500  signature bond, with conditions:
--to remain absolutely sober: no possession or ingestion of alcohol
--no presence in bars, taverns, liquor stores
--no operation of a motor vehicle without a valid drivers license 
--not to leave the State of Wisconsin
--The Defendant is to report and comply with SCRAM alcohol monitoring program as administered by Wisconsin Community Services.  The Court orders the defendant to SCRAM monitoring through WCS, with the consideration of Remote Breath as an alternative only when WCS verifies that a defendant's work environment or health condition prohibits the SCRAM bracelet.
The Defendant is to comply with all SCRAM Program conditions of participation including payment of program costs and fees.   **If in custody, release on SCRAM only.**
recess 3:08pm.
